title: Sick & Tired of Snow
desc:
A Fargo, North Dakota, man was arrested for clearing snow with

title: Mr. Rogers Rumor Neighborhood
desc: Fred Rogers served as a sniper during the Vietnam War and had a large number of confirmed kills.

title: COVID-19
desc: An article from January 2020, claiming to be from a local news station in North Dakota (Valley News Live), circulated on Facebook.

title: Why Doesn't America Read Anymore?
desc: On April 1, 2014, NPR posted an article to its Facebook page titled "Why Doesn't America Read Anymore?"

title: Chinese Lesbian Billionaires Marry
desc: In 2017, a tweet about two Chinese lesbian billionaires who married and became the world's richest couple went viral on Twitter.

desc: Image of Theodore Roosevelt riding a moose.

desc: In September 2017, Hillary Clinton released her memoir What Happened.

title: Facebook Hoaxes
desc: It's official: Facebook will start charging user fees.

title: Share to Get Money from Bill Gates
desc: Share a certain post of Bill Gates on Facebook and he will send you money.

title: Pope Francis Endorses Trump
desc: In 2016, a story circulated that Pope Francis made an unprecedented and shocking endorsement of Donald Trump for president.

desc: In August 2017, Hurricane Harvey hit and devastated areas of Texas and Louisiana.

title: Obama Seeks Third Term
desc: President Obama shocked the country when he announced he would be running for a third term.
